# Summary of Recommended Spec Revisions

| Spec Element | Current | Recommended Revision |
|---|---|---|
| **Lighthouse properties** | 5–10 | 1–2 lighthouse + 2–3 overlay partners |
| **Bundled-SKU-only** | Hold for 12 months | Hold for 25 weekends, but instrument waitlist for "stay-only" demand signal |
| **Founder-taught** | First 50 weekends across all properties | First 50 weekends across 2 properties max; supply ≤ facilitator capacity |
| **Privacy pillar** | "Your IP stays yours" | Narrow to "Your space is private"; publish data policy for managed keys; default BYO-key |
| **TAM framing** | Implicitly venture-scale | Explicitly plan as lifestyle business with expansion triggers |
| **Success criteria** | 50 weekends in 6 months | 25 weekends in 6 months (realistic for 2 properties) |
| **Phase 2 planning** | In v1 spec | Remove from v1; revisit at weekend 30 based on data |

### Three falsifiable predictions to track:
1. **Waitlist conversion:** ≥5% of waitlist sign-ups book within 60 days of property going live. If <5%, the product has a messaging or pricing problem.
2. **Rebooking rate:** ≥30% of couples rebook within 6 months. If <30%, the experience isn't sticky enough to sustain the business.
3. **TAM ceiling:** If you exhaust your launch metro's addressable couples (can't fill weekends without repeat bookings) within 9 months, the market is too thin for single-metro operation. Expand geography or expand persona.

