This also means: **the press-friendly version of the company doesn't exist in v1.** No cute name on the door. No photogenic lighthouse property. No "Couples That Code" hero shot. Just a Stripe link, a partner hotel, and a spreadsheet of NPS scores. If the kernel is real, we earn the right to build the brand layer afterward. If not, we saved 12 months and $300K finding out.

