## Final architectural plan

### Phase 0 — operating SKUs
- `Remote Sprint`: 3 hrs facilitated by video — deliver weekly
- `Venue Day`: 8 hrs at one primary partner venue (one city, one audited backup) — deliver alternate weeks
- `Weekend Retreat`: refundable deposit (~$250) — demand probe only, do not deliver

### Phase 0 — pass criteria (all required)
- `Remote Sprint` ≥3 deposits
- `Venue Day` ≥3 deposits
- Total deposits across SKUs ≥10
- `deposit / qualified leads` ≥30% for at least one delivered SKU
- `deposit / raw matched inquiries` ≥10% for at least one delivered SKU
- `Venue Day` beats `Remote Sprint` on either qualified-lead conversion OR gross profit per inquiry
- ≥3 `Weekend Retreat` deposits from couples who first bought a delivered SKU within 7 days
- Non-founder conversion ≥50% of founder-couple conversion

### Phase 0 — kill criterion
- 3 distinct campaign variants over 90 days, none meet the pass bar → kernel is dead

### Phase 0 → Phase 1 gating
- `Remote Sprint` underperforms → facilitation thesis fails → fold or pivot
- `Venue Day` does not beat `Remote Sprint` on conversion OR gross profit per inquiry → venue layer is theater → drop venue in v2
- Warm-buyer weekend deposits <3 → retreat thesis is dead → never operate weekends

### Phase 1 — begins only after Phase 0 passes (12-month window)
- Operate one live `Weekend Retreat` per month
- Continue `Remote Sprint` and `Venue Day` cadence
- Phase 1 gates (all required):
  - ≥50% contribution margin after venue + ops on the winning SKU
  - First-order CAC payback within one booking
  - ≥30% rebook within 12 months OR ≥0.5 organic referrals per booking
- If any Phase 1 gate fails → this is bespoke services; stay small or fold

### Operational definitions (locked before launch)
- `Raw matched inquiry`: both partners confirm they are a romantic couple, both engage with site or sales call, both confirm actively building or want to resume a paused shared project
- `Qualified lead`: raw matched inquiry + price shown + format explained + availability confirmed
- `Warm buyer`: paid deposit on a delivered SKU and either attended or is on calendar

### Founder-input decisions (not architectural)
- City: founder-network density, not market size
- Copy: A/B "build together" vs. "a productive date"
- AI: optional, subordinate in copy, surfaces in intake tooling-sync menu only

### Held back until Phase 1 passes
- Brand name (bland placeholder until then)
- Any press outreach
- Lodging ownership, lighthouse properties, certification track
- Romance framing in headline (only in A/B body copy)

### Permanently dropped
- Managed-token resale
- "Your IP stays yours" as brand pillar (replaced with "private space, your keys, your data" — feature-bullet only)
- "5–10 lighthouse properties in 6 months" supply plan
- Any plan that scales operating supply faster than facilitator capacity

## Bottom line

The architecture is locked. Execution is now: ship the landing page with three SKUs, sign one primary venue + one backup, lock the intake form to operationalize the denominators, and start the 90-day Phase 0 clock. No further architectural decisions remain — the next signal comes from paid deposits, not from spec revisions.

